               <msContents>
                  <summary>Ff. 1-226: Acts and Miracles of Saint Qawestos, abbott of Dabra Libanos (edited a few years ago in Studi e Testi 418)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="2r" to="115v"></locus>
                     <title ref="LIT1486GadlaQ"></title>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">The original colophon (copied with the text) states that this book of the gadl and miracles was composed by Abuna Mabāʻā Ṣeyon, the only surviving disciple of the saint, during the reign of Emperor Dāwit (1382-1413)</colophon>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                     <locus from="2r" to="109r"></locus>
                     <title>Gadl</title>
                     </msItem>
